        <p>Common questions from content teams and SEO managers comparing keyword tools. More? Email <a href="mailto:founder@thestacc.com">founder@thestacc.com</a>.</p>
        <p style="margin-top: 24px;">See more: <a href="/reviews/" class="accent">read tool reviews</a>, <a href="/alternatives/" class="accent">compare alternatives</a>, or <a href="/pricing/" class="accent">view pricing</a>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the best keyword research tool in 2026?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">It depends on what you need. If you want keyword research turned into published content automatically, theStacc plans your full monthly calendar and publishes 30 articles for $99/month. For raw keyword databases, Semrush leads with 26 billion keywords. Ahrefs has the most accurate difficulty scores. Budget-conscious users should start with Mangools at ~$31/month.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can you do keyword research for free?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. Google Keyword Planner provides keyword volume and competition data directly from Google at no cost. Ubersuggest offers 3 free searches per day. The limitations are data precision (ranges instead of exact numbers) and missing difficulty scores. Free tools work best when paired with at least one paid tool.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How much do keyword research tools cost?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Prices range from free (Google Keyword Planner) to $499/month (Serpstat Agency). The practical range for most businesses is $29–$250/month. Mangools starts at ~$31/month. Semrush starts at $139/month. Annual billing saves 15–35% on most tools.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is Google Keyword Planner enough for SEO?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">For basic keyword discovery, yes. For competitive analysis and difficulty scoring, no. Google Keyword Planner shows volume ranges instead of exact numbers and has no keyword difficulty metric. It's best used as a supplement to a paid tool, not a replacement.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the most accurate keyword research tool?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Ahrefs has the most accurate keyword difficulty scores because they're calculated from actual backlink data of ranking pages. For search volume accuracy, all tools estimate. Cross-referencing Google Keyword Planner with a paid tool gives the most reliable picture.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is keyword research still important in 2026?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. 96.55% of all pages get zero traffic from Google — mostly because they targeted the wrong keywords. AI search has changed how results appear, but keyword intent still drives what content gets surfaced. Long-tail keywords convert at 2.5x the rate of head terms and account for over 90% of all searches.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do I need both Ahrefs and Semrush?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Most teams don't need both. Ahrefs specializes in backlink analysis and keyword accuracy. Semrush functions as an all-in-one platform. Choose Ahrefs for link-focused work; choose Semrush if you need keyword research, site audits, and PPC data alongside link building.</div>
